335
00:17:00,603 --> 00:17:01,603
Where is that?

336
00:17:01,813 --> 00:17:04,648
And Henley, could I please
have a random seat number?

337
00:17:05,608 --> 00:17:07,108
Oh. Lucky number 13.

338
00:17:07,318 --> 00:17:08,944
- B-5-13. Where are you?
- (AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

339
00:17:09,153 --> 00:17:12,781
Sir, please, stand up. Ah, there you are. Hi.

340
00:17:14,408 --> 00:17:18,203
Could you just confirm for me that this
is, in fact, your seat? B-5-13.

341
00:17:18,287 --> 00:17:19,246
Yes.

342
00:17:19,330 --> 00:17:21,331
Okay. Wonderful.
Now, could you please tell us

343
00:17:21,457 --> 00:17:22,791
your name and the name of your bank?

344
00:17:22,959 --> 00:17:25,168
Well, my name is Etienne Forcier.

345
00:17:25,419 --> 00:17:28,797
And my bank, it's Credit Republicain de Paris.

346
00:17:28,965 --> 00:17:30,131
French. Okay. Uh...

347
00:17:30,341 --> 00:17:31,800
We were hoping for something
a little more local,

348
00:17:31,968 --> 00:17:34,219
a kind of mom-and-pop
credit union with no security.

349
00:17:34,303 --> 00:17:36,263
But that's fine. A promise is a promise.

350
00:17:36,472 --> 00:17:37,639
Could you please come up to the stage

351
00:17:37,723 --> 00:17:39,057
- and we'll rob your bank.
- (CHEERING)

352
00:17:39,141 --> 00:17:41,017
And while he does that...

353
00:17:41,310 --> 00:17:44,437
There is someone here tonight
without whom we would just be

354
00:17:44,522 --> 00:17:47,649
four magicians working the circuit,
trying to get...

355
00:17:47,817 --> 00:17:49,234
Well, actually, trying to get here.

356
00:17:49,318 --> 00:17:52,237
You probably know this man,
if not from one of the many, many

357
00:17:52,321 --> 00:17:53,405
companies he puts his name on.

358
00:17:53,489 --> 00:17:57,117
He is our friend. He is our benefactor.
Mr. Arthur Tressler.

359
00:17:57,201 --> 00:17:59,160
Please, stand up, Art. Please, stand up.

360
00:17:59,370 --> 00:18:02,163
MERRITT: The only man here with
the Queen's cell phone number.

361
00:18:03,124 --> 00:18:05,125
Actually, please, stay standing, Art.

362
00:18:06,168 --> 00:18:08,295
I want to say that when we came
to Mr. Tressler,

363
00:18:08,504 --> 00:18:12,090
we promised that, as a unit, we could become
the biggest name in magic.

364
00:18:12,174 --> 00:18:13,717
HENLEY: So we wanted to say, "Thank you."

365
00:18:13,801 --> 00:18:15,635
And by the way, Art,
you notice on the sign out front,

366
00:18:15,720 --> 00:18:17,637
we made sure we put your name on top.

367
00:18:18,014 --> 00:18:22,100
If you turn out to be as good
as you think you are, dear girl,

368
00:18:22,184 --> 00:18:24,227
that won't be necessary much longer.

369
00:18:24,478 --> 00:18:25,729
HENLEY: We haven't done our closer yet.

370
00:18:25,980 --> 00:18:26,980
- (GRUNTS)
- Why don't you watch it

371
00:18:27,064 --> 00:18:28,273
and then you can decide for yourself.

372
00:18:28,357 --> 00:18:30,609
Ladies and gentlemen, Arthur Tressler!

373
00:18:30,693 --> 00:18:32,360
DANIEL: Thank you.
And, of course, once again,

374
00:18:32,445 --> 00:18:34,404
the Cardinal of Clairvoyance,
Merritt McKinney.

375
00:18:34,906 --> 00:18:38,116
Etienne, what Jack
is bringing to the stage now,

376
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:41,828
is what we in the magic world
call a teleportation helmet.

377
00:18:42,038 --> 00:18:48,084
You will need to wear this, as it will allow you
to literally fold through space and time

378
00:18:48,336 --> 00:18:50,503
to your bank in the...

379
00:18:50,713 --> 00:18:51,713
8th?

380
00:18:51,923 --> 00:18:53,840
- 9th arrondissement.
- Yeah.

381
00:18:54,050 --> 00:18:58,011
Now, once you are there, we will be able
to speak with you through this helmet.

382
00:18:58,095 --> 00:18:59,846
- Now if... Ah!
- Ow.

383
00:19:00,056 --> 00:19:01,723
- Oh, my God, that's beautiful.
- (AUDIENCE CHUCKLING)

384
00:19:01,891 --> 00:19:04,684
It has the added attraction of being
very stylish.

385
00:19:04,769 --> 00:19:08,229
It's about time the French learned
from America on that subject.

386
00:19:09,565 --> 00:19:10,690
Is that a beautiful piece of headgear?

387
00:19:10,775 --> 00:19:12,400
- Thank you. Thank you...
- It is.

388
00:19:13,444 --> 00:19:16,029
Thank you. Thank you very much.

389
00:19:16,113 --> 00:19:17,322
<i>MERRITT: Mais oui. Mais oui.</i>

390
00:19:17,406 --> 00:19:18,740
But before you go anywhere,

391
00:19:18,866 --> 00:19:20,992
could you please, pick a card, any card.

392
00:19:21,077 --> 00:19:22,077
Not that card. Oh!

393
00:19:22,411 --> 00:19:25,830
No, that's an old American joke.
You can take that one.

394
00:19:25,915 --> 00:19:27,374
Okay. This one?

395
00:19:27,583 --> 00:19:29,542
Show it to your friends in Section B.
But not to us.

396
00:19:31,379 --> 00:19:33,380
Okay, great.
Now if you could just sign your name there.

397
00:19:33,464 --> 00:19:35,882
- Yes.
- In English, if possible.

398
00:19:36,258 --> 00:19:37,634
- MERRITT: That's good.
- Thanks.

399
00:19:38,761 --> 00:19:39,886
Put it in your pocket.

400
00:19:40,262 --> 00:19:42,639
And now for one tiny detail.

401
00:19:44,100 --> 00:19:46,226
(AUDIENCE GASPING)

402
00:19:50,940 --> 00:19:52,482
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

403
00:20:00,074 --> 00:20:04,619
Now, Etienne, let's step into
this cockamamie contraption.

404
00:20:04,829 --> 00:20:06,746
And I'll step off of it. Bonne chance.

405
00:20:07,164 --> 00:20:10,041
It's 11:50 p.m. Here in Vegas.

406
00:20:10,126 --> 00:20:14,796
That's 8:50 a.m. In Paris.
Your bank opens in less than 10 minutes.

407
00:20:15,006 --> 00:20:16,047
One,

408
00:20:16,132 --> 00:20:17,173
two...

409
00:20:17,258 --> 00:20:18,299
Three.

410
00:20:20,136 --> 00:20:21,177
(ALL GASPING)

411
00:20:21,595 --> 00:20:22,804
MERRITT: What the fuck?

412
00:20:22,972 --> 00:20:24,597
- Wow! Etienne?
- Whoa. Etienne?

413
00:20:24,807 --> 00:20:26,641
It wasn't supposed to happen
like that, was it?

414
00:20:26,809 --> 00:20:27,851
HENLEY: Etienne?

415
00:20:28,477 --> 00:20:30,478
I liked that little French guy.

416
00:20:30,646 --> 00:20:31,688
Where did he go?

417
00:20:31,814 --> 00:20:33,314
(CARS HONKING)

418
00:20:40,656 --> 00:20:42,198
Wait, there he is.

419
00:20:44,493 --> 00:20:46,536
No, no, no, no, please, please, please.

420
00:20:46,787 --> 00:20:48,663
This is Daniel Atlas. Can you hear me?

421
00:20:49,540 --> 00:20:51,958
- Etienne? Are you okay?
- Yes.

422
00:20:52,043 --> 00:20:54,419
Perfect. What do you see in there?

423
00:20:56,380 --> 00:20:57,505
Money.

424
00:20:58,007 --> 00:20:59,007
Is this real?

425
00:20:59,175 --> 00:21:01,676
Yes. Looks like three million or so
Euros' worth.

426
00:21:02,386 --> 00:21:03,678
(SPEAKS FRENCH)

427
00:21:03,888 --> 00:21:05,638
Okay, now, here's what
we're gonna need you to do.

428
00:21:05,723 --> 00:21:09,225
<i>I want you to take the card that you signed</i>
out of your pocket.

429
00:21:09,351 --> 00:21:11,519
And I want you to take the ticket stub
from tonight's show

430
00:21:11,729 --> 00:21:13,897
<i>and I want you to put it right there</i>
in the middle of the money.

431
00:21:18,027 --> 00:21:19,194
Now drop it.

432
00:21:31,207 --> 00:21:34,334
Now, on the side of your helmet
you should feel a button.

433
00:21:34,543 --> 00:21:35,710
Don't press it just yet.

434
00:21:35,920 --> 00:21:40,507
That button activates an air duct
that connects Paris to Las Vegas.

435
00:21:40,716 --> 00:21:42,050
<i>Okay, good. Now you can press it.</i>

436
00:21:42,218 --> 00:21:45,762
All right, now, Etienne, hold on tight.
You might feel a bit of a vacuum.

437
00:21:45,846 --> 00:21:46,846
(CHUCKLES)

438
00:21:48,099 --> 00:21:49,766
(AIR WHOOSHING)

439
00:21:54,438 --> 00:21:55,563
(WHOOPS)

440
00:22:03,739 --> 00:22:05,365
Whoo! (LAUGHING)

441
00:22:16,919 --> 00:22:18,253
Oh. Wait a second.

442
00:22:18,462 --> 00:22:19,879
- Huh.
- (RUMBLING)

443
00:22:31,058 --> 00:22:32,559
WOMAN: Oh, merde.

444
00:22:32,977 --> 00:22:34,602
(CHEERING)

445
00:22:52,246 --> 00:22:53,413
(CHUCKLES)

446
00:22:57,418 --> 00:22:58,626
(LAUGHING)

447
00:23:11,974 --> 00:23:13,808
Thank you, Etienne. Thank you, everyone!

448
00:23:14,310 --> 00:23:15,435
We are The Four Horsemen.

449
00:23:15,644 --> 00:23:17,937
- And good night!
- Good night!

450
00:23:26,488 --> 00:23:27,947
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

451
00:23:30,743 --> 00:23:31,951
Hold up here.

452
00:23:32,328 --> 00:23:33,620
Dylan Rhodes.

453
00:23:35,414 --> 00:23:37,415
What? I don't think I heard you correctly.

454
00:23:37,625 --> 00:23:38,958
Did you say magicians?

455
00:23:39,168 --> 00:23:40,793
Yeah, Dylan, magicians.

456
00:23:41,170 --> 00:23:42,253
<i>Where are you now?</i>

457
00:23:42,463 --> 00:23:44,339
I'm at Aria.
I'm heading up there to grab 'em now.

458
00:23:48,677 --> 00:23:50,470
FBI! Hands where I can see them.

459
00:23:50,679 --> 00:23:51,971
Let's go. Get 'em up. Come on.

460
00:23:52,139 --> 00:23:53,139
<i>Uno minuto.</i>

461
00:23:53,432 --> 00:23:55,141
FULLER: Let's go. Get 'em up.

462
00:23:55,351 --> 00:23:56,643
Put the book down.

463
00:23:56,852 --> 00:23:58,478
Okay. You got me.

464
00:23:58,687 --> 00:24:00,104
- Freeze! Hands in the air!
- HENLEY: (GASPS) Oh, my!

465
00:24:00,689 --> 00:24:03,441
Do one of you guys
mind giving us a hand with our bags?

466
00:24:03,984 --> 00:24:04,984
Let's go.

467
00:24:10,658 --> 00:24:12,283
(PEOPLE APPLAUDING)

468
00:24:22,836 --> 00:24:24,671
<i>DYLAN: Boss, please tell me this is a joke.</i>

469
00:24:24,880 --> 00:24:27,799
<i>I just got Willy Mears</i>
to finger Paulie Attanasio.

470
00:24:28,008 --> 00:24:31,261
I'm a month, two tops,
away from blowing this whole thing open.

471
00:24:31,345 --> 00:24:33,513
- Get Turkelson.
- He's in Atlantic City.

472
00:24:33,681 --> 00:24:36,391
What about Cowan? Look at him.
He's just sitting there on his ass.

473
00:24:36,517 --> 00:24:37,725
Hilarious, Rhodes.

474
00:24:38,185 --> 00:24:39,310
I love you.

475
00:24:39,645 --> 00:24:40,687
Asshole.

476
00:24:40,896 --> 00:24:42,313
I don't have time for this magic crap.

477
00:24:42,523 --> 00:24:45,066
This crap just pulled
three million Euro out of a Parisian bank.

478
00:24:45,150 --> 00:24:46,234
- That's how much they got?
- Yeah.

479
00:24:46,402 --> 00:24:47,902
Actually, 3.2.

480
00:24:51,907 --> 00:24:53,283
- Who is she?
- (MUMBLES)

481
00:24:53,575 --> 00:24:54,575
Who are you?

482
00:24:54,660 --> 00:24:57,829
Alma Dray from Interpol.
I'll be working the investigation with you.

483
00:24:58,038 --> 00:24:59,080
You gotta be kidding me.

484
00:24:59,290 --> 00:25:02,000
It's bad enough they got me chasing down
David Copperfield and Friends.

485
00:25:02,209 --> 00:25:05,295
Now I'm being saddled with,
no offense, with Interpol?

486
00:25:05,504 --> 00:25:07,588
I look forward to working
with you, too, Agent Rhodes.

487
00:25:07,798 --> 00:25:10,675
I'm sorry. I don't think I'm gonna
need your help on this. Okay?

488
00:25:10,884 --> 00:25:12,885
- Where's the French guy?
- I already spoke to him.

489
00:25:13,512 --> 00:25:15,888
Oh, you did?
You spoke to my witness before me?

490
00:25:16,098 --> 00:25:19,100
Your witness?
I thought you didn't want the case.

491
00:25:19,310 --> 00:25:20,893
Besides, he's useless.

492
00:25:21,103 --> 00:25:22,645
Oh, really? Why is that?

493
00:25:22,855 --> 00:25:25,023
Because he believes their magic was real.

494
00:25:25,232 --> 00:25:28,276
Oh, he believes the magic was real?
You're right, he probably is useless.

495
00:25:28,485 --> 00:25:31,404
Is it okay with Interpol if we talk to him, too?

496
00:25:31,488 --> 00:25:33,072
- Mm-hmm.
- Thank you.

497
00:25:34,116 --> 00:25:37,201
I have never stolen a thing in my life, okay?

498
00:25:37,411 --> 00:25:39,620
I tried to give the money back,
but they won't take it.

499
00:25:39,872 --> 00:25:42,332
Okay, okay, okay,
let's just say you robbed a bank.

500
00:25:42,416 --> 00:25:43,583
I did.

501
00:25:43,751 --> 00:25:44,959
Fine. Fantastic. You did.

502
00:25:45,085 --> 00:25:47,628
But since I'm new to this,
can you explain to me how you went

503
00:25:47,713 --> 00:25:50,131
from Las Vegas to Paris in three seconds?

504
00:25:50,549 --> 00:25:52,675
With the teleportation helmet.

505
00:25:52,926 --> 00:25:54,344
Okay, what the hell is going on here?

506
00:25:54,470 --> 00:25:56,137
